title: Artificially de-bounce lock requests by 1 second
message:
Artificially de-bounce lock requests by 1 second

In multiwindow mode, we can enter a loop where the user unlocks,
receives a multiwindow switch event, and re-locks the same screen

This occurs most commonly when the user is not using any timeout

We work around this issue by artificially adding one second to the
timeout time whenever an unlock has occurred. This should prevent the
UI from interrupting the user.

title: When the lock screen opens, keep record of it
message:
When the lock screen opens, keep record of it

When lock screen comes into view (onStart) add it to a map of open lock screen entries.
When the lock screen is created agin, check if that window already exists and if so,
attempt to close it by a call to finish()

This should prevent multiple windows from opening for the same application in freeform/multiwindow mode
and should also solve some of the freeform ugly bugs

The downside, is we use a static map which holds Activity instances. This screams bad design.
To try and soften this terrible design, we at least make sure we only hold weak references to the
activity instance so it can hopefully be GCed faster

message:
Fix a bug where whitelisting would whitelist the PACKAGE and fail

Whitelist does not need to update existing entries because a whitelisted entry is the same as 'no entry'
but with the additional caveat that a new entry will not be created because a whitelisted one exists.

As such, when whitelisting we can just call an insert and assume that even if a previous entry exists,
it will now simply be whitelisted.

title: Rework how package and activity locking works
message:
Rework how package and activity locking works

The switch on the lock list toggles a package based lock. Once a package is entered and unlocked,
no other activities will prompt for the lock code unless the activity is specifically locked in the
LockInfoDialog for that package.

This should prevent the lock screen from popping up too many times and should still preserve the security of the application

title: Update to use latest pydroid
message:
Update to use latest pydroid

The new pydroid has some backwards incompatable changes
for one, strong references to the views are now held, so we dont need to null check
as a result, we must make sure to honor the activity lifecycle always so that we do not leak

instead of overriding the bindView/unbindView methods directly, which can be error prone if one forgets to
call through to the super method, the new blank hooks for onBind and onUnbind will be populated.

onResume and onPause do not change.

title: Fix bug where info dialog doesn't display
message:
Fix bug where info dialog doesn't display

Reproduce:

Launch PadLock
Click Settings
Click back
Click any entry

Result:
No info dialog shows up

WeakReference is cleared onDestroyView but the fragment itself persists. onCreate is
not called again so the Adapter is not re-initialized, leaving a NULL ref weak reference.

Fix by holding strong reference to Fragment from Adapter, which should only live for as long as
it is attached to view, which is within lifecycle
